result.execSummary:
The defendant Tracy Lee Larson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant, Tracy Lee Larson appeared with Attorney Thomas O. Mulligan.  Attorney Thomas H Frost appeared for the State.  Also has 14 CT 44 and 14 TR 667.   Court calls cases and recites appearances.  State recites plea - G/NC to OWI and G/NC to poss. THC strike repeater makes it a misd. with 1 year probation.  Atty Mulligan agrees.  Court has Atty Mulligan speak to his client in private to see if there is an agreement.  8:41 AM  - Back on the record at 8:42 - Atty Mulligan states client has no further questions.  Court questions Ms. Larson as to plea questionnaire.  Court grants motion to amend 14 CF 71 and delete the repeater 961.41(3g)(b).  Defendant entered plea of NC to 14 CF 71 and 14 CT 44.  Court finds defendant guilty fo 14 CF 71 and 14 CT 44.  State argues sentencing.  Atty Mulligan argues sentencing.  

COURT:   14 TR 667 is dismissed
14 CF 71:  sentence w/held probation 1 year - costs - maintain absolute sobriety - AODA and any conditions DOC may impose along with DNA sampe and surcharge. 

14 CT 44:  $1494.00 - 45 days in county jail 1st 48 hours in custody balance on voice recognition monitor to begin today with good time and huber - dl revoked 24 months retro to admin. susp. and AODA
